subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Re: Unicode proposal again.
msgSnippet: Yes, Quikscript is a B1 script so realistically it ll have to go in the SMP. Shavian already has code points assigned there (10450-1047F).
messageBody:
Yes, Quikscript is a B1 script so realistically it'll have to go in the SMP.
Shavian already has code points assigned there (10450-1047F).

Ph.D. wrote:
>
> Just to be sure I'm clear on this:
> We're talking about assigning QS and Shavian
> to code points in Plane 1, right?
>
> --Ph. D.
>
>
